============================================================================
A) ABOUT ELSI
============================================================================

   ELSI provides and enhances open-source software packages which solve or
   circumvent the Kohn-Sham eigenvalue problems in the self-consistent field
   cycle of density-functional theory.

   Visit the ELSI Interchange website for more information:

     http://elsi-interchange.org

   For questions, please email:

     elsi-team@duke.edu

============================================================================
B) INSTALLATION OF ELSI
============================================================================

   The standard installation process of ELSI requires:

   * A Fortran 2003 compiler
   * A C compiler supporting the C99 standard
   * A C++ compiler supporting the C++11 standard
   * An MPI library
   * LAPACK and ScaLAPACK
   * PtScotch 6.0.4
     (recommended, availabel at https//gforge.inria.fr/projects/scotch)
     or ParMETIS 4.0.3
     (available at http://glaros.dtc.umn.edu/gkhome/views/metis)
   * SuperLU_DIST 5.1.3
     (available at http://crd-legacy.lbl.gov/~xiaoye/SuperLU)

   GNU, Intel, PGI, XL, and Cray compilers are supported.

   The user specifies their system environment via flags set in a "make.sys"
   file, which should be placed in the root directory of ELSI alongside the
   Makefile.  Some example "make.sys" files that the user may adapt for
   their own system environment are available in the "./make_sys" folder.

   The compilation process is:

   * make
   * make check (optional)
   * make install

   Please refer to the "INSTALL" file for the complete installation process.

